-- Spot gold hits session low after U.S. income data
-- 
-- Mon Apr 30, 2012 8:48am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2012/04/30/us-markets-precious-data-idUSBRE83T0JM20120430

 

 LONDON  (Reuters) - Spot gold hit a session low on Monday, after U.S. data showed household income rose in March by the most in three months, while spending increased only modestly. 
 Spot gold hit $1,644.50 an ounce, down 1 percent against $1,662.32 late on Friday. The precious metal later recovered slightly to trade at $1,650.30 an ounce at 1244 GMT. (Reporting by Harpreet Bhal)